-# Locals: organization, teammate, employee_name (optional)
- organization = local_assigns.fetch(:organization)
- teammate = local_assigns.fetch(:teammate)
- employee_name = local_assigns[:employee_name].presence || teammate.person.casual_name

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    Capture how #{employee_name} is doing on position, assignments, and aspirational values in one pass—and see how assignment energy splits across the whole role (~100% total).

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  = render 'shared/maap/definition'
  = render 'shared/check_ins/three_step_clarity_flow', organization: organization, teammate: teammate, employee_name: employee_name

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Bulk clarity check-in
  %p.mb-2
    This screen is Step One (
    = link_to 'Reflect Apart', organization_company_teammate_check_ins_path(organization, teammate)
    ) for everything at once. Employee and manager each work their side; view mode shows whose draft you are editing.
  %p.mb-0
    Use the assignment energy bars in the Assignments section to see planned tenure split (left) vs reflection % (right). The right bar updates as you change energy dropdowns.
